{
  "texts": [
    "31 also investigated the predictability of Bitcoin and the profitability of trading strategies derived from several machine learning algorithms (e.g., linear models, SVM, and random forests).",
    "Their positive results further support the robustness of machine learning in terms of the predictability and profitability of Bitcoin, even in challenging market environments.",
    "Historical data consisting of past price movements, trading volumes, and other relevant market information have proven to be valuable resources for traders and investors attempting to develop effective trading strategies that would allow them to make informed decisions in the volatile Bitcoin market 20.",
    "Numerous studies have shown the potential of using historical data in conjunction with analytical techniques, such as technical analysis and machine learning algorithms.",
    "These tools enhance the performance of trading strategies and accuracy of price prediction 32."
  ]
}